===Intransitive Verb===
{{en-verb|babbl|ing}}

# To [[utter]] words indistinctly or unintelligibly; to utter [[inarticulate]] [[sound]]s; as, a child ''babbles''.
# To [[talk]] [[incoherently]]; to utter unmeaning words.
# To talk much; to [[chatter]]; to [[prate]].
# To make a continuous [[murmur]]ing noise, as shallow water running over stones.
#:*In every '''babbling''' brook he finds a friend. - [[Wordsworth]].
#:''Hounds are said to '''babble,''' or to be '''babbling,''' when they are too noisy after having found a good scent.''

